TITLE: Rendering React Email and Sending via Postmark SDK (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to use the Postmark Node.js SDK to send an email created with React Email. It imports the 'render' function to convert the React 'Email' component into an HTML string. It then initializes the Postmark client using an API key (stored in environment variables), defines email parameters (sender, recipient, subject, HTML body), and calls the 'sendEmail' method to dispatch the email.
SOURCE: https://github.com/resend/react-email/blob/canary/apps/docs/integrations/postmark.mdx#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { render } from '@react-email/components';
import postmark from 'postmark';
import { Email } from './email';

const client = new postmark.ServerClient(process.env.POSTMARK_API_KEY);

const emailHtml = await render(<Email url="https://example.com" />);

const options = {
  From: 'you@example.com',
  To: 'user@gmail.com',
  Subject: 'hello world',
  HtmlBody: emailHtml,
};

await client.sendEmail(options);
```

