TITLE: Using @react-email/html in a React Email Template
DESCRIPTION: Sample React component demonstrating how to import and embed the Html component from @react-email/html within an email layout, including setting the language attribute and adding a styled Button. The Html component wraps the email content for consistent formatting across email clients.
SOURCE: https://github.com/resend/react-email/blob/canary/packages/html/readme.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Button } from "@react-email/button";
import { Html } from "@react-email/html";

const Email = () => {
  return (
    <Html lang="en">
      <Button href="https://example.com" style={{ color: "#61dafb" }}>
        Click me
      </Button>
    </Html>
  );
};
```

