TITLE: Importing and Rendering a Code Block in React Email Component - JSX
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to import the CodeBlock component and a theme (dracula) from @react-email/code-block, then render a syntax-highlighted code block within a React functional email component. The code prop receives a JavaScript source string, with optional lineNumbers, theme, and language props for customization. This requires @react-email/code-block as a dependency, and the input JavaScript code can be any valid string to display. The rendered output appears as a styled, highlighted block in email-compatible HTML.
SOURCE: https://github.com/resend/react-email/blob/canary/packages/code-block/readme.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { CodeBlock, dracula } from "@react-email/code-block";

const Email = () => {
  const code = `export default async (req, res) => {
  try {
    const html = await renderAsync(
      EmailTemplate({ firstName: 'John' })
    );
    return NextResponse.json({ html });
  } catch (error) {
    return NextResponse.json({ error });
  }
}`;

  return (
    <CodeBlock
      code={code}
      lineNumbers // add this so that there are line numbers beside each code line
      theme={dracula}
      language="javascript"
    />
  );
};
```

