TITLE: Using the Markdown Component in React Email
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use the Markdown component within a React Email template. It imports the Markdown and Html components from the @react-email library and renders Markdown content with custom styles for headings and container. Two usage examples are given, one using the `children` prop as a string and the other demonstrating how custom styles are applied.
SOURCE: https://github.com/resend/react-email/blob/canary/packages/markdown/readme.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Markdown } from "@react-email/markdown";
import { Html } from "@react-email/html";

const Email = () => {
  return (
    <Html lang="en" dir="ltr">
      <Markdown
        markdownCustomStyles={{
          h1: { color: "red" },
          h2: { color: "blue" },
          codeInline: { background: "grey" },
        }}
        markdownContainerStyles={{
          padding: "12px",
          border: "solid 1px black",
        }}
      >{`# Hello, World!`}</Markdown>

      {/* OR */}

      <Markdown children={`# This is a ~~strikethrough~~`} />
    </Html>
  );

```

