TITLE: Using React Email Font component in template (jsx)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to integrate the `@react-email/font` component into a React Email template. It imports necessary components (`Html`, `Head`, `Font`) and uses `Font` within the `<Head>` tag to define a custom font family, fallback fonts, and a web font URL with format. This sets the font for the entire email.
SOURCE: https://github.com/resend/react-email/blob/canary/packages/font/readme.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { Html } from "@react-email/html";
import { Head } from "@react-email/head";
import { Font } from "@react-email/font";

const Email = () => {
  return (
    <Html lang="en">
      <Head>
        <Font
          fontFamily="Roboto"
          fallbackFontFamily="Verdana"
          webFont={{
            url: "https://fonts.gstatic.com/s/roboto/v27/KFOmCnqEu92Fr1Mu4mxKKTU1Kg.woff2",
            format: "woff2",
          }}
        />
      </Head>
    </Html>
  );
};
```

